div.p:
Herewith, dear Mr. Macdonald, I send you the just received document;
See [J. Whitment] to M, 6 May 1890. see printout – should this be J. Forrest?
the second report, to which Mr. Forrest alludes, was not in the envelope, nor has it as yet come separately. I wrote him already some weeks ago, that it was quite useless to enquire at the coast, as the light-colored aborigine has his tribe near Warburton's track, and as the death-place of the four people was still very much farther inland.
